A severe storm has hit Madrid on Monday evening causing flash floods in the area. The Guardian reported that following the flash flooding and hail, parts of eastern Spain and the Balearic is expected to have heavy rainfall. The heavy violent storm has also brought roads to a standstill, BBC reported. There were no reported injuries. Flash floods and hail hit Spain Cars were washed away as torrents of water flowed through neighbourhoods in Madrid. Compiled by Naseema Barday GET THE NEWS at your fingertips and download the News24 app for Android here now. Get it for your iPhone here. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter 